President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Rachel Elise Barkow and Judge Charles R. Breyer as Commissioners of the United States Sentencing Commission. Barkow is currently a professor at the New York University School of Law and focuses on criminal and administrative law. Breyer is a United States District Judge in the Northern District of California. Additionally, President Obama intends to appoint Thomas Murray as a member of the Cultural Property Advisory Committee. Murray is an expert in Indonesian sculpture and textiles and is the founder of a private gallery of tribal, Asian, and textile art.